<div id="review_1273171502" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1273171502" />
    <a title="Brittany" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12252811-brittany"><img alt="Brittany" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1517865853p2/12252811.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1273171502?book_show_action=true">May 06, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Brittany" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Brittany" href="/user/show/12252811-brittany">Brittany</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12252811-brittany?shelf=pride-and-prejudice">pride-and-prejudice</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12252811-brittany?shelf=will-read-again">will-read-again</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1273171502" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9816038805004451795">This was an interesting adaptation where Darcy doesn&apos;t propose in Hunsford, as Elizabeth finds out that one of her sisters dies. Darcy then is compelled to take Elizabeth back to Hertfordshire to be with her family.<br/><br/>I actually give this book a 3.5, or maybe a 3.75 lol. It&apos;s just not quite to four for me. I guess my biggest complaint is just Elizabeth&apos;s attitude in the beginning of the book. She is just beyond rude to Darcy. Elizabeth is rude in P&amp;P, but not when he actually is nice being downrigh</span>
  <span id="freeText9816038805004451795" style="display:none">This was an interesting adaptation where Darcy doesn't propose in Hunsford, as Elizabeth finds out that one of her sisters dies. Darcy then is compelled to take Elizabeth back to Hertfordshire to be with her family.<br /><br />I actually give this book a 3.5, or maybe a 3.75 lol. It's just not quite to four for me. I guess my biggest complaint is just Elizabeth's attitude in the beginning of the book. She is just beyond rude to Darcy. Elizabeth is rude in P&amp;P, but not when he actually is nice being downright nice to her. I've a read a few books where I feel like they take Elizabeth's anger and goes out of control with it. I know the author would probably explain that she did this because Elizabeth never received his letter, and therefore was still harboring the anger of how he split up Jane and Bingley and how he ruined Wickham's life. But she snaps at him a lot when he is being sweet...and that doesn't work for me. <br /><br />However, less than halfway through the book some of the misunderstandings are cleared up, and she does, of course, start falling for Darcy (hopefully you don't consider that a spoiler...). From there the book is sweet and lovely. They add in a little more drama too which is always fun. I love that the author tries to heal Mr. and Mrs. Bennet's relationship too. I also love Georgianna in this retelling. She really plays a major roll in fixing everything.<br /><br />I will read again :)</span>
  <a data-text-id="9816038805004451795" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


