    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_686531238" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/686531238" />
    <a title="Patricia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1103251-patricia"><img alt="Patricia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1360605131p2/1103251.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/686531238?book_show_action=true">Aug 05, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Patricia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Patricia" href="/user/show/1103251-patricia">Patricia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1103251-patricia?shelf=read-in-2017">read-in-2017</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1103251-patricia?shelf=read-in-2020">read-in-2020</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer686531238" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16388282842948371225">What a wonderful Pride and Prejudice variation. Before Darcy can propose to Elizabeth in Kent, she receives terrible news that her youngest sister, Lydia has fallen while walking with Wickham, Kitty and Denny and has died. Instead of a disastrous proposal Darcy is able to comfort a devastated Elizabeth, and even offers to take her home. Through these new circumstances, Lizzy begins to realize that her negative impressions of Darcy may be wrong.<br/><br/>The whole story was addictive and I couldn&apos;t put it </span>
  <span id="freeText16388282842948371225" style="display:none">What a wonderful Pride and Prejudice variation. Before Darcy can propose to Elizabeth in Kent, she receives terrible news that her youngest sister, Lydia has fallen while walking with Wickham, Kitty and Denny and has died. Instead of a disastrous proposal Darcy is able to comfort a devastated Elizabeth, and even offers to take her home. Through these new circumstances, Lizzy begins to realize that her negative impressions of Darcy may be wrong.<br /><br />The whole story was addictive and I couldn't put it down. The romance is gradual, compelling and extremely satisfying. You would think with all the variations I have read that I would get sick of this story, but it is novels like this one that take the beloved story and create something new and interesting. Jane Austen created such wonderful lovers in Darcy and Elizabeth that I never get tired of seeing what would happen in their lives with just a few changes to the their original story. <br /><br />The addition of grief in Elizabeth's family changes not only her opinion of Darcy, but also the relationship of others in her family. I loved the new relationship between Mr. and Mrs. Bennet. It was so touching and extremely satisfying in the end. This is a book that I will reread many times in the future, and I'm so glad that I decided to give it a chance.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16388282842948371225" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review686531238">
  <td colspan="2">
