              <span id="reviewTextContainer587787901" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer145357868353740598">What a lovely variation, very original! I&apos;ve read lots of variations in which Mr. Bennet has died, or sometimes Mrs. Bennet, but never before Lydia. This is a very tender story about grief, love and reconciliation. I loved this Mr. Darcy, going out of his way to assist Lizzy and the Bennets in their loss. Georgiana was also a great character, she was quite the matchmaker! </span>
  <span id="freeText145357868353740598" style="display:none">What a lovely variation, very original! I've read lots of variations in which Mr. Bennet has died, or sometimes Mrs. Bennet, but never before Lydia. This is a very tender story about grief, love and reconciliation. I loved this Mr. Darcy, going out of his way to assist Lizzy and the Bennets in their loss. Georgiana was also a great character, she was quite the matchmaker! </span>
