            <span class="readable">&ldquo;Elizabeth laughed and pushed her father's shoulder. "Go, Papa, and be kind to him. I love him so. And it would be to your advantage to be on his good side." <br />Mr. Bennet raised his eyebrows. "Oh, and why is that?" <br />Because I have seen both his libraries in London and at Pemberley, Papa."<br />Interested and amused, Mr. Bennet said, "Ahh, and are they very grand, Lizzy?"<br />A more exquisite sight you will not see," she assured him.&rdquo;</span>
